sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM fouls 
WHERE foul_result = 'free throw';

external_knowledge:
- 'team' refers to the team named '<TeamName>';
- 'their big day' corresponds to the date '<GameDate>';
- The total score is the sum of points scored by the team in all plays of the game.

Key teams refer to the Chicago Bulls and the Los Angeles Lakers;
Fall of 2017 spans from October 1, 2017, to December 31, 2017;
Regular season games are the standard matches not including playoffs or championships.

sql:
SELECT timeout_id, game_id, team_id, half, time_remaining_half, secs_remaining, secs_remaining_absolute, timeout_length, timeout_reason
FROM timeouts
WHERE timeout_length > 5 AND team_id = 1;

SELECT player_id, player_name, team_id, position, jersey_number, height, weight, draft_year, draft_round, draft_pick
FROM players
WHERE player_id IN (SELECT player_id FROM assists);

SELECT game_id, final_home_score
FROM games
WHERE final_home_score - final_away_score >= 2;

SELECT player_id, COUNT(*) AS total_assists
FROM assists
GROUP BY player_id;

SELECT final_win_prob 
FROM games 
WHERE game_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "battles" metaphorically refers to games;
- "New Year" implies January 1, 2022;
- "battleground" is metaphorical for the game venue;
- "final scores" are represented by final_home_score and final_away_score columns;
- "score margins" are the final_score_diff;
- "likelihood of the home team emerging victorious" refers to the final_win_prob;
- "season of these encounters" is represented by the season_id;
- "chronological order" means the games are ordered by date.

- Significant assists refer to plays recorded in the database as significantly impacting the game's score;
- A large margin and a considerable amount both mean a score difference of more than 5 points;
- The term 'team' refers to either the home team or the away team depending on the context of the game.
